I"<ol>
  <li>Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a non-stick frying pan over medium heat. Cook sausages, in batches, for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned. Transfer to a plate.</li>
  <li>Add remaining oil to pan and add onion and cook for 4 minutes or until soft. Add curry paste, flour and apple. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Gradually stir in stock. Bring to the boil. Return sausages to pan and simmer for 2 minutes or until heated through.</li>
  <li>Spoon rice onto plates. Top with curried sausages and coriander. Serve.</li>
</ol>
